{{Use dmy dates|date=July 2013}} {{Use British English|date=December 2010}} {{Infobox award | name = BBC Young Dancer | current_awards = | image = | imagesize = | caption = | description = Exceptional dancing talent | presenter = [[BBC|British Broadcasting Corporation]] (BBC) | country = United Kingdom | year = 2015 | year2 = | website = [http://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/b07gbzxt BBC Young Dancer website] }} '''BBC Young Dancer''' is a televised national [[Competitive dance|dance competition]], broadcast on [[BBC Four]] and [[BBC Two]] since 2015. The competition, inspired by the success of the biennal [[BBC Young Musician of the Year]], is designed for British amateur dancers of [[ballet]], [[Contemporary dance|contemporary]], [[Hip-hop dance|hip hop]] and South Asian dance, all of whom must be aged between 16 and 20.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://bbc.co.uk/news/entertainment-arts-29442240|title=BBC launches contest to find future dance stars|publisher=BBC News|date=2 October 2014|accessdate=16 January 2015}}</ref>
BBC Young Dancer was launched in October 2014 by [[Director-General of the BBC]], [[Tony Hall, Baron Hall of Birkenhead|Tony Hall]] and was part of BBC Four's Year of Song and Dance. Cuban ballet dancer [[Carlos Acosta]] was the competition's ambassador. On 14 January 2015, ballet dancer and ''[[Strictly Come Dancing]]'' judge [[Darcey Bussell]] was announced as co-presenter and dance expert for the Grand Final of the inaugural competition, which was aired live from [[Sadler's Wells Theatre]] on [[BBC Two]] in May. [[Zoë Ball]] and [[Clemency Burton-Hill]] were her co-hosts.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.theguardian.com/media/2015/jan/14/darcey-bussell-front-bbc-search-uk-best-young-dancer |title=Darcey Bussell to front BBC’s search for UK’s best young dancer |work=The Guardian |location=UK |date=14 January 2015 |accessdate=16 January 2015}}</ref> Contemporary dancer Connor Scott won the inaugural competition on 9 May 2015.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/entertainment-arts-32680433 |title=BBC Young Dancer: Connor Scott named as first winner |work=BBC News |publisher=BBC |date=9 May 2015 |accessdate=10 May 2015}}</ref>
The next competition was held in 2017, contemporary dancer Nafisah Baba was announced as the winner of the overall title on 22 April.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-39683255 |title=Nafisah Baba wins BBC Young Dancer 2017 prize |work=BBC News |publisher=BBC |date=23 April 2017 |accessdate=23 April 2017}}</ref> The televised grand final was hosted by Bussell, [[Anita Rani]] and [[Ore Oduba]].
