'''Old Cotabato City Hall Museum''' is a city museum fronting Rizal Park Plaza in [[Cotabato City]], Philippines. The structure was built in 1940s as the Municipal Hall of former Municipality of Cotabato also served as the visitors information center.
==History== Built in 1940s under the leadership of the former Cotabato Mayor Jose Lim, later dubbed as Cotabato City Hall in 1960s when the Municipality of Cotabato is recognized as a City.
Designed by the Filipino architect Juan Arellano<ref>{{cite news|last1=Sembrano|first1=Edgar|title=Juan Arellano: The architect, artist and master builder|url=http://www.tribune.net.ph/life-style/juan-arellano-the-architect-artist-and-master-builder|accessdate=8 January 2018|work=The Daily Tribune|date=8 January 2018}}</ref> before the war, this building is a legacy of neo vernacular architecture.
==Exhibits== <gallery> Cotabato City Museum 2.jpg|Brass ware a city product Cotabato City Hall Museum Exhibit 12.jpg|Kulintang one of the traditional musical instrument in Cotabato Cotabato City Hall Museum Exhibit 15.jpg|Bamanan Cotabato City Hall Museum Exhibit 8.jpg|Artifacts exhibited in the Museum Cotabato City Hall Museum Exhibit 9.jpg|Another artifacts including gong and banga Cotabato City Hall Museum Exhibit 7.jpg|Batil a talagadan, antique talam holder together with palnus a talagadan, used during the pagana (feast) festival, among the Maguindanao and Maranao. Cotabato City Hall Museum Exhibit 3.jpg|One the design of famous “Inaul fabric” Cotabato City Hall Museum Exhibit 10.jpg|Inaul and artifacts are exhibited on the 2nd floor Cotabato City Hall Museum Exhibit 11.jpg|Portrait of former elected vice mayors of Cotabato City hanged on the wall Cotabato City Hall Museum Exhibit 13.jpg|Entrance of the Museum
</gallery>
The museum houses the city’s historical artifacts, pioneer families heirlooms, and other noteworthy pieces of history such as vintage photos and books.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://sox.explora.ph/attraction/709/cotabato-city-s-old-city-hall|title=Cotabato City's Old City Hall|website=Sox.explora.ph|accessdate=7 January 2018}}</ref>
